olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet dried oregano
2 clove garlic
1 packet chicken thigh
½ onion
1 tsp honey
1 carrot
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
¼ cup vinegar (white wine or red wine)

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut the potato into bite-sized chunks, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with the dried oregano and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the potatoes are baking, finely chop the garlic. In a medium bowl, combine the garlic, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add the chicken thigh, then season with salt and pepper. Turn to coat and set aside.

Thinly slice the red onion (see ingredients). In a small bowl, combine the vinegar and a good pinch of salt and sugar. Scrunch the onion in your hands, then add to the pickling liquid with just enough water to cover the onion. Set aside.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook the chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side. Remove the pan from the heat, then add the honey and turn the chicken to coat. Transfer the chicken to a second lined oven tray and bake until cooked through, 8-12 minutes (depending on size).

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, grate the carrot.
Finely chop the tomato. Drain the pickled onion
(reserve some pickling liquid for the dressing).
In a medium bowl, combine the carrot, tomato,
pickled onion, mixed salad leaves, a dash of the
pickling liquid and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to
taste and toss to coat.

Slice the garlic and herb charred chicken. Divide the chicken, oregano potatoes and Greek salad between plates. Crumble the cheese over the salad. Serve with the mayonnaise.